<br>
She opens her eyes to see a mermaid and a siren almost upon her bearing their terrible weap-  Uh - Soap?  And a scrub brush???  Their eyes are full of mischief, and they begin to pull off Mircha's clothes.  She feels the hands holding her relax their grip, and let go, only to grab her waist, and spin her around.  She comes to a stop facing the creature who dragged her down.  She is quite prepared to be furious with her attacker and punish them for this prank, and is glaring when she is faced with a merman.  A merman with a smile that would melt chocolate, and eyes like the purest emerald.  And hands that are no longer gripping her firmly, but gently.  Hands that are touching her bare skin.  Mircha blushes furiously, and drops her eyes, only to raise them again.  She wants to memorize this face so that she can do it justice in a ballad.<br>
<br>
She surrenders herself to their ablutions, and the warmth with which they are given.  Finally, the merman caresses her once more, and lifts her to the shore.  She sits a moment on the shore, lost in remembrance of the very recent past, until the cold of the morning bites into her wet and naked body.  She rises, and swiftly dons her cloak, thankful to have at least one dry item of clothing.  She grabs her backpack, and wraps her wet clothing up in a bundle.  A glint of metal catches her eye, and she picks it up.  It is a codpiece!  What strange things are here, she thinks.  Dropping the metal to the ground, she picks up the wet bundle, and heads away from the pond to find some wood.  She is greatly in need of a fire.<br>
<br>
